Transnet tugs and fire-fighters are currently battling a blaze aboard a cargo ship that has anchored in Algoa Bay. Smoke can be seen billowing from the ship with Transnet tug boats assisting.Port Elizabeth Harbour Master Captain Brynn Adamson said: We are still assessing the situation and are assisting where we can .Adamson said the vessel has 21 crew members. Non-essential personnel have been evacuated.